3 - Core features

    Currently, the VNiX Operating System uses Cuoreterm for the framebuffer. Cuoreterm is a super lightweight and freestanding framebuffer made by JerryJhird
    for CuoreOS. VNiX also features RISCV32 program support, made by Dcraftbg. For more information about either one of these project, visit the links below:
    This OS also features the Limine Bootloader, because of its extensive features and ease of use. I personally support its goals and achievements, which is why
    I've included it in this project.

    Links:                v v v
    CuoreOS: https://github.com/jerryjhird/CuoreOS
    Cuoreterm: https://github.com/jerryjhird/Cuoreterm
    rv_vm.h: https://codeberg.org/Dcraftbg/rv_vm.h


4 - Required dependencies 

    Below are the required dependencies for building this project from scratch:

    make
    parted
    qemu-system-x86_64
    gcc
    ld



